summary: Behind the Scenes of Silence in the Library/Forest of the Dead (Part Seven) Excerpt from the DVD commentary with David Tennant,...
caption:
Behind the Scenes of Silence in the Library/Forest of the Dead (Part Seven)

Excerpt from the DVD commentary with David Tennant, Julie Gardner, and Steven Moffat:

JG: David, when a Steven Moffat script arrives, are there distinguishing things?
SM: …it’s very late
DT: [ laughs ]
JG: Are there more words?  Are there lots of words?
DT: There are a lot of words…
JG: More than average or not?
DT: No, I wouldn’t say necessarily more on average. Steven and Russel both share a propensity for making the Doctor go off on one…
SM & JG: [ laughs ]
DT: …but in that way that you love, because you get of weave in these kind of brilliant speeches.  It takes a bit longer to learn…
SM: I do think about that sometimes when I’m typing away absolute nonsense - I think, David’s gonna be in that wee flat going, “Oh, I don’t even know what this means!”
DT: [ big laugh ] It’s never absolute nonsense though, is it?
SM: Well it’s certainly got less of a relationship with anything else than any other long speech you’re gonna learn, even in Hamlet 

Excerpt from the Forest of the Dead podcast commentary featuring David Tennant, Russell T. Davies, and Steven Moffat:  

RTD: So who is River Song, Steven?
[all laugh]
SM: The Doctor’s Mum, at last revealed
[more laughter]
SM: Well, who knows.  Well, I know…
DT: How is Alex Kingston’s availability for 2009?
SM: Extensive
DT: Do you think we’ll see her again?
SM: Could do
[more laughter]
RTD: Like the Time Traveler’s Wife, isn’t it?
SM: Yeah
RTD: She could crop up anywhere at any time.  It’s beautiful, and we’re laughing here because none of us likes to pin down exactly who she is.   If you say who she is, you spoil it.
DT: And the script doesn’t - very particularly the script doesn’t.

title: Tenth Doctor - New Changes
body:
Can you please do an doctor who imagine with the 10th doctor? Where the doctor and the reader is married but Donna and Martha (think she is in the episode) are still there? And that some how goes along with the episode? Season 4 episode The doctor daughter.

A/N: I’ve never actually watched this show, nor do I have access to it. I tried to use Wiki but it’s one of those shows that you have to watch to understand. There for I had to switch the prompt up a bit. Sorry :/. Enjoy! -Julianne  

The wedding was something if not magical, in your eyes. To get to marry the love of your life was something most people couldn’t do. 

Of course you knew that after the wedding your life would no longer be a piece of cake, but that’s thought didn’t worry you too much. 

You wanted now to be just the joy of being married. Your eyes scanned the room as you watched your families and friends dance around. Smiles and giggles were all round. 

“I think we should eat some more cake.” You husband laughed. 

Before you could answer you felt the creamy icing touch your cheek. A smile formed on your face, as you scooped the icing off your face, and placed it in your mouth. 

“Okay, but now it’s my turn.” You giggled before taking a glop of the icing and placing in on the doctor’s nose.  

You two were nothing but giggled, as you kept up the fun. 

~

The worst part about the day after your wedding was the fact that your husband had to leave for travel. You knew he had no choice, but that didn’t really matter. 

“You know if I could, I would stay here in bed with you all day.” He cooed as he placed his pants back on. 

“I know.” You sighed, deciding you should get up knowing that Donna and Martha would be over soon to take your husband. 

“Do want me to make some coffee, before you leave?” 

“Don’t have time, but thank you.” He smiled, before giving you a kiss. Before you could say anymore there was a knock on the front door. 

“I’ll get that, you finish getting ready.” 

You left your husband, and opened the door to see two smiling girls. Donna, handed you some flowers, as Martha smiled. 

“We know that it’s not much but we figured it was something to make you smile. “Martha said. They each gave you a hug. 

“Thank you ladies.” You smiled. “Please, make sure he comes back in one pieces.” You halfheartedly joked. 

“Are you ladies talking about me?” Your husband teased as he walked into the living room. 

“Always.” You laughed. You leaned up to kiss his cheek. “Be careful. I love you.”

“I love you too, and I’m always careful.” 

“Sure…” Donna and Martha said at the same time.

-Julianne

A/N: I’ve never actually watched this show, nor do I have access to it. I tried to use Wiki but it’s one of those shows that you have to watch to understand. There for I had to switch the prompt up a bit. Sorry :/. Enjoy! -Julianne  

The wedding was something if not magical, in your eyes. To get to marry the love of your life was something most people couldn’t do. 

Of course you knew that after the wedding your life would no longer be a piece of cake, but that’s thought didn’t worry you too much. 

You wanted now to be just the joy of being married. Your eyes scanned the room as you watched your families and friends dance around. Smiles and giggles were all round. 

“I think we should eat some more cake.” You husband laughed. 

Before you could answer you felt the creamy icing touch your cheek. A smile formed on your face, as you scooped the icing off your face, and placed it in your mouth. 

“Okay, but now it’s my turn.” You giggled before taking a glop of the icing and placing in on the doctor’s nose.  

You two were nothing but giggled, as you kept up the fun. 

~

The worst part about the day after your wedding was the fact that your husband had to leave for travel. You knew he had no choice, but that didn’t really matter. 

“You know if I could, I would stay here in bed with you all day.” He cooed as he placed his pants back on. 

“I know.” You sighed, deciding you should get up knowing that Donna and Martha would be over soon to take your husband. 

“Do want me to make some coffee, before you leave?” 

“Don’t have time, but thank you.” He smiled, before giving you a kiss. Before you could say anymore there was a knock on the front door. 

“I’ll get that, you finish getting ready.” 

You left your husband, and opened the door to see two smiling girls. Donna, handed you some flowers, as Martha smiled. 

“We know that it’s not much but we figured it was something to make you smile. “Martha said. They each gave you a hug. 

“Thank you ladies.” You smiled. “Please, make sure he comes back in one pieces.” You halfheartedly joked. 

“Are you ladies talking about me?” Your husband teased as he walked into the living room. 

“Always.” You laughed. You leaned up to kiss his cheek. “Be careful. I love you.”

“I love you too, and I’m always careful.” 

“Sure…” Donna and Martha said at the same time.

-Julianne
